Meet Our Team





Meet Our Team

Bob Rachlow - FSA, MAAA






	Bob has been involved in the investment and insurance arena for over 25 years, covering nearly every aspect of product development, pricing and design for investment and insurance products, ranging from annuities and life insurance, to reinsurance and group health, to complex investment vehicles such as Mortgage-Backed Securities (MBSs) and Collateralized Mortgage Obligations (CMOs).  This unique blend of experience has provided Bob with the tools necessary to successfully help his clients as they navigate the complex financial world.


	Bob currently serves as the Chief Operating & Chief Compliance Officer of Capstone Advisors, LLC, a registered investment advisory firm, advising on $70 million of assets under management.  Bob and a group of four other seasoned investment professionals founded the firm in 2000, all after having successful careers at a large international institutional company.  In his capacity at Capstone, Bob is responsible not only for the day-to-day operations of the firm, but is in charge of compliance and regulatory issues, as well as serving both individual and institutional client’s investment needs and goals.


	Prior to starting Capstone, Bob served as a Vice President and Director of the Quantitative Research Group for a nationally recognized investment firm, where he was responsible for the strategic direction of pricing, performance and benchmarks for nearly $38 billion of fixed‑income assets.


	An actuary by professional training, Bob is a Fellow of the Society of Actuaries and a Member of the American Academy of Actuaries.  He earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Actuarial Science from the University of Iowa and is a graduate of the Emerging Leader Development Program at Columbia University’s Graduate School of Business.


	Bob and his wife, Darlene, and their two boys – Aaron and Nathan – attend Oak Park Church, where Bob has served as a Deacon.  In his free time, Bob enjoys SCUBA diving and umpiring high school and college baseball.


Email Bob »





Scott Krafft - CFA, CPA (NON-PRACTICING), AIF






	     Scott is a trusted source of financial counsel for clients, helping them successfully navigate the turbulent waters of the financial markets over the past decade. He is skilled in designing globally diversified portfolios and helping individuals understand and manage their behavior, helping them reach their retirement years successfully.  Clients owning small businesses benefit from Scott’s wisdom earned over 30 years of diverse professional experience spanning many financial disciplines.


	     Scott serves as the President and a founding member of Capstone Advisors, LLC, a registered investment advisory firm that launched in November of 2000.  The team of seasoned investment professionals brought years of broad institutional experience from Delaware Investment Management Company, the institutional investment arm of Lincoln Financial Corporation.  The founders had a vision to reach the underserved private client, small endowment/foundation and retirement plan markets, offering a professional, fee-only, consultative model and advice based on the academic research foundational to the widely held principles of modern finance.


	     In addition to ongoing financial economic research, Scott assist’s the client team in developing investment policy and managing investment portfolios for families and trusts, designing risk-based investment portfolios for retirement plans, and consulting as an investment fiduciary to retirement plan sponsors.


	     Recent events has directed Scott’s time to research portfolio risk management, fiduciary duty for 401(k)/Profit Sharing Plans and family wealth transition. He achieved the globally recognized Chartered Financial Analyst™ (CFA®) designation in 1998, holds his license as a Certified Public Accountant (CPA), and has also earned the Accredited Investment Fiduciary (AIF®) designation (specializing in Fiduciary review of retirement plans). He has also served as guest lecturer in finance and business ethics at Taylor University.


	     Prior to founding Capstone, Scott spent 10 years at Delaware Investments and Lincoln Financial Group as an investment officer in the mezzanine finance unit, dedicated to direct investment in privately held companies going through leveraged buyouts, co-investing with private equity funds and investing in private equity partnerships.  He began with Lincoln in 1991 as a commercial mortgage loan officer covering mortgage investment in the northeast region of the US.  He was hired from Society National Bank in Cleveland, Ohio where he established a commercial mortgage brokerage unit.


	     After graduating magna cum laude in accounting from Youngstown State University in 1982, Scott spent 4 years working on the audit and tax staffs of the national accounting firm, Ernst & Whinny.  He earned his CPA license in 1986.


	     Scott and his wife, Beverly, are active in their community and serving their local church. Scott has served various leadership capacities on non-profit boards including chairman of the elder board at North Park Community Church. Scott and Bev enjoy spending time with their four children: Amanda, Andrew, Aaron, and Anna; watching son Andy dive at the collegiate level. He also finds time for jogging; reading; and officiating high school and college football.


Email Scott» 





Josh Jerele - Portfolio Advisor






	As a Portfolio Advisor, I am committed to building rapport with our clients and assisting them with understanding the ins and outs of their financial lives. Our clients would expect to work along side of me as we will develop their unique plan that will allow them to reach their goals.  Most importantly, my goal is to give our clients peace of mind.


	I was born and raised in Columbus, Ohio. I graduated from Taylor University with a Bachelors of Science in finance.  During my time at Taylor, I studied a variety of disciplines abroad in England, China, and Paraguay.  After graduation I moved to Fort Wayne and joined the Capstone team.  I met my wife Jillian while attending Taylor University in 2010 and we were married in June 2012.  We enjoy serving in the community and spending time with family and friends.


